Pour milk into large bowl. Add dry pudding mixes and 3/4 cup of the coconut. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Gently stir in 1 cup of the whipped topping. Pour into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Spread pie with remaining 1 cup whipped topping. Toast remaining 1/4 cup coconut, if desired. Sprinkle over pie. Store leftover pie in refrigerator.